      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    gaṇācariyānaṃ therānaṃ bha<lb n="2" break="no"/>yaṃta<persName key="pers:BhSulasa">sulasānaṃ</persName>
	    tevijā<lb n="3" break="no"/>naṃ aṃtevāsinaṃ therāna
	  <lb n="4"/>
	    bhayaṃta <persName key="pers:BhCetiyasa">cetiyasānaṃ</persName> tevi<lb n="5" break="no"/>jānaṃ
	    naṃdanakānavaka
	  <lb n="6"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 unit="character"
		 quantity="3"
		 precision="low"/>a ko<app><lem>tha</lem><note resp="#CTI">The letter tha had at first been 
	    omitted and then cut above the line.</note></app>lakī
	  <lb n="7"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 unit="character"
		 quantity="3"
		 precision="low"/>ca gahapati
	  <lb n="8"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 unit="character"
		 quantity="4"
		 precision="low"/>natuno <persName key="pers:Nandanaka">nadaṇaka</persName>
	  <lb n="9"/>
	    <gap reason="lost"
		 unit="line"
		 quantity="1"/>
	  <lb n="10"/>
	    deyadhama
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  The Ācārya of the Gaṇa, the Venerable (Thera) and Reverend (Bhayanta)
	  Tevidya <persName key="pers:BhSulasa">Sulasa</persName>:
	  his discipline Thera Bhayanta 
	  <persName key="pers:BhCetiyasa">Chetiyasa</persName>, a Tevidya...
	  nadanakāṇavaka... kothalakī... and householder... his grandson 
	  <persName key="pers:Nandanaka">Nandanaka</persName>...
	  the meritorious gift.
	</p>
      </div>
